                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-295-off1590 t18260406-295-victim1590"></join>
                  </persName>
             and others, his partners.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-295-person1591">
                  HENRY 
                  BATTEN
               <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1591" type="surname" value="BATTEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1591" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1591" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am clerk in the employ of Messers. Pickford and Co. I received a truss from the Angel Inn, Fleet-market, on Thursday, the 23d of February, directed to 
               <persName id="t18260406-295-person1592">
                  Joshua 
                  Lever
               <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1592" type="surname" value="Lever"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1592" type="given" value="Joshua"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1592" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , Bolton, Lancashire; we were to convey it to Manchester.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-295-person1593">
                  JAMES 
                  POWNER
               <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1593" type="surname" value="POWNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1593" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1593" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am clerk to Messrs. Pickford. On the evening of the 23d of February I was in the office, at the Castle Inn, Wood-street, and saw the prisoner come off the shafts of a waggon, with a truss on his shoulder - it was going to the City basin, and was directed to James Lever, Bolton. I followed him, and stopped him in Wood-street; the truss fell and I fell - he ran away; I followed, and called Stop thief! I saw him in a few minutes, and have no doubt of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-295-person1594">
                  THOMAS 
                  DAVIS
               <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1594" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1594" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1594" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the employ of Messrs. Pickford and Co. I loaded a truss on their waggon in the yard on the 23d of February, about half-past ten o'clock; on the fore part of it - it was directed to Joshua Lever, Bolton, Lancashire.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-295-person1595">
                  JAMES 
                  GREIVES
               <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1595" type="surname" value="GREIVES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1595" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1595" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On this evening I was at my door, opposite the gateway. I heard the cry of Stop thief! ran out, and saw the truss in the street; I took it up - the witness ran after the prisoner, down Love-lane, and in a minute afterwards I saw him brought back.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-295-person1596">
                  JAMES 
                  HARRISON
               <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1596" type="surname" value="HARRISON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1596" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1596" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I work for Messrs. Pickford. I saw Grieves take the truss up, and brought it to the office while the prisoner was in the yard.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-295-person1597">
                  JOHN 
                  BARNES
               <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1597" type="surname" value="BARNES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1597" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1597" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I received the prisoner and this truss.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-295-person1598">
                  JAMES 
                  POWNER
               <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1598" type="surname" value="POWNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1598" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-295-person1598" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This is the truss - it is the property of Messrs. Pickford and Co - Zachary Langton is one of their partners.</p>
